4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE MOTOR VEHICLE REGISTRATION TRAUMATIC
5 BRAIN INJURY DONATION LAWS; PROVIDING FOR THE USE OF THE FUNDS TO EDUCATE AND
6 SUPPORT INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES LIVING WITH TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURIES; CHANGING THE
7 CONTRIBUTION TO AN AUTOMATIC DONATION WITH AN OPT-OUT PROVISION; PROVIDING FOR
8 NOTICE; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 2-15-2218, 33-22-2104, 61-3-303,
9 AND 61-14-101, MCA.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 Section 1. Section 2-15-2218, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "2-15-2218. Traumatic brain injury account. (1) There is a traumatic brain injury account in the
15 state special revenue fund for purposes of traumatic brain injury prevention, education, and support.
16 (2) Money in this account may be used by the department of public health and human services to
17 fund the advisory council and to provide grants for public information and prevention education regarding
18 traumatic brain injury for funding activities that educate and support recovery of individuals and families,
19 including military service personnel, living with traumatic brain injuries, promote brain injury prevention, and
20 support the traumatic brain injury advisory council."
21
